%h2 Overview

%p
  mpv is a fork of mplayer2 and MPlayer. It shares some features with
  the former projects while introducing many more.

.row
  .col-md-6
    %h4
      %i.fa.fa-terminal
      Streamlined CLI options
    %p
      MPlayer's options parser was improved to behave more like other CLI
      programs, and many option names and semantics were reworked to make
      them more intuitive and memorable.

  .col-md-6
    %h4
      %i.fa.fa-play
      On Screen Controller
    %p
      While mpv has no official GUI, it has a small controller
      that is triggered by mouse movement.


  .col-md-6
    %h4
      %i.fa.fa-play
      Multiple GUI choices
    %p
      Why include a built-in GUI and reduce choice
      possibilities?
      mpv has a plethora of GUIs available for those that
      prefer it over a CLI.
      %p
      - Multiplatform:
      %a(href="https://github.com/u8sand/Baka-MPlayer")Baka 
      %a(href="http://smplayer.sourceforge.net")SMPlayer
      %a(href="http://ovoplayer.altervista.org")OvoPlayer
      %a(href="https://github.com/kanishka-linux/kawaii-player")Kawaii-Player
      %a(href="https://github.com/cmdrkotori/mpc-qt")mpc-qt
      %a(href="https://github.com/kokoko3k/xt7-player-mpv")Xt7-player-mpv
      %p
      - %i.fa.fa-mac Mac: %a(href="https://lhc70000.github.io/iina/")IINA
      - %i.fa.fa-android Android: 
      %p
      %a(href="https://github.com/mpv-android/mpv-android")mpv-android  
      %p
      Please look
      %a(href="https://github.com/mpv-player/mpv/wiki/Applications-using-mpv#gui-frontends")here
      for a more complete list.

  .col-md-6
    %h4
      %i.fa.fa-bolt
      Very high level of customizability
    %p
      mpv is highly customizable by the use of:
      - User Scripts: Lua, JavaScript, VapourSynth and GLSL.
      - Plugins: Built from C.
